23 Section 8. That § 10-12-43 be AMENDED:
24 10-12-43. The governing body of the school district may raise additional revenues
25 for general fund purposes only, from property tax through the imposition of an excess tax
26 levy. The governing body of a school district may impose the excess tax levy with an
27 affirmative two-thirds vote of the governing body on or before July fifteenth of the year
28 prior to the year the taxes are payable. On any excess tax levy approved after July 1,
29 2002, the governing body of the taxing district shall specify in the resolution the year or
30 number of years the excess tax levy will be applied.
31 The requirements for an announcement made pursuant to this section are as
32 follows:
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1323E 5 1323
1 (1) The decision of the governing body to originally impose or subsequently
2 increase an excess tax levy shall be first published within ten days of the decision;
3 (2) Publication shall be made at least twice in the legal newspaper designated pursuant
4 to § 13-8-10, with no fewer than five days between publication dates, before the
5 opt out takes effect;
6 (3) The announcement shall be at least three newspaper columns in width and four
7 inches in length or at least one-sixth of a page in size, whichever size is greater;
8 (4) The announcement shall be headed with the following statement in a typeface no
9 less than eighteen point type: "ATTENTION TAXPAYERS: NOTICE OF PROPERTY
10 TAX INCREASE OF $(fill in amount)." The remainder of the announcement shall
11 consist of a reproduction of the "Resolution for Opt Out," including the amount that
12 property taxes will be increased annually by the proposed opt out and a statement
