26 voters voting at the last preceding general election, for districts with more than five
27 thousand registered voters. Petitions in districts with less than five thousand registered
28 voters must be signed by five percent of the total number of registered voters at the last
29 preceding general election. The board in scheduling the opening day of classes shall allow
30 sufficient time for the referendum process authorized in this section.The registered voters
31 of a school district may refer a resolution adopted by the board of a school district to
32 schedule the first day of classes before the first Tuesday following the first Monday in
33 September by filing with the business manager of the school district, a petition signed by
34 at least five percent of the registered voters of the school district, based upon the total
