1 number of registered voters in the school district at the last preceding general election,
2 within thirty days of the adoption of the resolution.
3 Section 15. That § 13-64-7 be AMENDED:
4 13-64-7. A decision by a school board to implement a school sentinel program
5 pursuant to § 13-64-1 may be referred to a vote of the qualified voters of the school
6 district by the filing of a petition signed by five percent of the registered voters in the
